      "comment_id" : 44720826,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "What if the default Locale is something like German, where a comma denotes a decimal place?  You could pass in, for example &quot;1,000,000&quot; which wouldn&#39;t parse into German Locale and would then be replaced by &quot;1.000.000&quot; which is not a valid Double."
