      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "The initial question said <i>&quot;Is there a better way to parse &quot;1,234&quot; to get 1.234 than: p = p.replaceAll(&quot;,&quot;,&quot;.&quot;);&quot;</i>, if you think <code>replace</code> significantly differs from using <code>replaceAll</code>, please explain why."
    } ],
