    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 20,
    "last_activity_date" : 1483439485,
    "creation_date" : 1483439485,
    "answer_id" : 41441444,
    "question_id" : 4323599,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<pre><code>Double.parseDouble(p.replace(',','.'))\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>...is very quick as it searches the underlying character array on a char-by-char basis. The string replace versions compile a RegEx to evaluate.</p>\n\n<p>Basically replace(char,char) is about 10 times quicker and since you'll be doing these kind of things in low-level code it makes sense to think about this. The Hot Spot optimiser will not figure it out... Certainly doesn't on my system.</p>\n"
  }, {
